    <note>Zhang(1) Shan [271] Ancestors were Fanyang jun (Zhuozhou, Liao territory) Zhang(1). His great grandfather, Congshi [3165], moved to Jinan, Licheng xian in order to avoid the disorder of the Five Dynasties. He was granted lands in the area, but neither he nor his son held any office. Shan's father, Yun [3180], who rose from a common soldier to be a military officer died in 1011. Both Shan and his brother, Kui(4) [3151], earned the jinshi and pursued careers in the civil bureaucracy. XCB, 176.5b, 180.19a; SS, 333.4b-5a; Song Qi, WJ, 57.12a; Wang Gui, WJ, 40.12b. CBD, 3, 2279.</note>
